	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Ninja Gaiden boss rush hack</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I got the idea yesterday that it would be kinda cool if there was a boss rush mode in Ninja Gaiden, which happens to be one of my favorite NES games. So I decided to go ahead and hack the ROM so that you only play the boss stages.<br /><br />You'll start the game with the fire weapon and 25 in spiritual strength. Spiritual strength will not be regained until after a game over, so I suggest that you save it until stage 6-4, or you're likely to get your rear end handed to you.<br /><br />If you want to try out the hack you can get the IPS file <a href="http://jiggawatt.org/NINJA_GA_BOSS_RUSH.zip" class="postlink">from here</a>. It's based on a dump named NINJA_GA.NES (262,287 bytes), which is the U.S. version. It might work with the European/Japanese version as well, but I haven't tried it.<br /><br />Further improvements could be e.g.:<br />* Automatically skipping the cutscenes so that you don't have to press the start button in between stages.<br />* Only regaining half of the energy lost in between stages, to make it a bit more challenging.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


